This paper proposes a new loss function for improving semantic segmentation, which is a task commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of backpropagation for tuning the loss function, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the importance of handling class imbalance, which is a common issue in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a softmax function, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method using various datasets, which is a common practice in natural language processing (cs.CL).
